pouch boundary-line patch 0019 - path-stat via SYS_stat (POUNCE).

Routes musl's stat(path)/lstat(path)/fstatat(path) family onto the
Thylacine-native SYS_stat (= 88; docs/POUNCE-DESIGN.md section 7): one
syscall whose resolution is the stalk walk-query -- on the disk FS a
single fused Twalkgetattr RPC with no handle/Spoor/fid ever created.

Before this patch the whole path-stat family was an ENOSYS hole: upstream
musl funnels stat/lstat through __fstatat -> SYS_statx/SYS_newfstatat,
both parked at the 0xFFFF sentinel by the 0001 seam (only fstat(fd) was
live, via 0010). Now:

  - stat(path) / lstat(path) / fstatat(AT_FDCWD, path, st, flags) work
    (lstat == stat at v1.0: no symlinks, G11).
  - fstatat(fd, "", st, AT_EMPTY_PATH) delegates to the 0010 fstat(fd).
  - a RELATIVE path against a real dirfd stays -ENOSYS (fail-closed; the
    kernel has no dirfd-relative stat surface at v1.0) -- exactly the
    pre-patch disposition for that form.

The t_stat -> struct stat translation is byte-identical to 0010's
fstat.c (the one source shape); the t_stat mirror struct is pinned by a
_Static_assert against the kernel's 80-byte ABI.

Depends on: 0001 (the seam), 0010 (fstat + the translation precedent).
