+/*
+ * pouch fstatat() -- route the PATH forms onto the Thylacine-native
+ * SYS_stat (= 88; the POUNCE walk-query, docs/POUNCE-DESIGN.md section 7)
+ * and translate the 80-byte struct t_stat into musl's aarch64 struct stat
+ * (the exact 0010-pouch-fstat-lseek translation, one source shape).
+ *
+ * The upstream fstatat is the statx/newfstatat trampoline the whole musl
+ * stat() family funnels through (stat -> fstatat(AT_FDCWD, path, buf, 0);
+ * lstat -> AT_SYMLINK_NOFOLLOW; fstat's AT_EMPTY_PATH arm was already
+ * bypassed by 0010). Both Linux syscalls are 0xFFFF ENOSYS sentinels under
+ * the 0001 seam, so pouch stat(path)/lstat(path) were ENOSYS holes until
+ * this patch. Now:
+ *
+ *   - dirfd == AT_FDCWD: SYS_stat(path, len, &t_stat). The kernel joins a
+ *     relative path with the Territory cwd (LS-4) -- exactly AT_FDCWD's
+ *     meaning. AT_SYMLINK_NOFOLLOW is accepted and identical (no symlinks
+ *     at v1.0, G11: stat == lstat).
+ *   - an absolute path with any dirfd: the dirfd is ignored per POSIX.
+ *   - a RELATIVE path against a real dirfd: -ENOSYS (fail-closed; the
+ *     kernel has no dirfd-relative stat surface at v1.0 -- unchanged from
+ *     the pre-patch behavior where EVERY form was ENOSYS).
+ *   - AT_EMPTY_PATH with an empty path: delegate to fstat(dirfd) (the
+ *     0010-patched SYS_fstat path).
+ */
